{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-awesome-all-timeline-js","path":"/2017/09/16/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Track Awesome List"}},"allAwesomeItem":{"nodes":[{"awesomeListRepo":"hangtwenty/dive-into-machine-learning","categoryHTML":"<h2><a href=\"https://www.coursera.org/learn/machine-learning\">Recommended course: Prof. Andrew Ng's <em>Machine Learning</em> on Coursera</a></h2><h3>Tips for studying</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>Busy schedule? Read <a href=\"https://rayli.net/blog/data/coursera-machine-learning-review/\">Ray Li's review of Prof. Andrew Ng's course</a> for some helpful tips.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-09-16T23:18:47.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"hangtwenty/dive-into-machine-learning","categoryHTML":"<h2><a href=\"https://www.coursera.org/learn/machine-learning\">Recommended course: Prof. Andrew Ng's <em>Machine Learning</em> on Coursera</a></h2><h3>Tips for studying</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>Review some of the <a href=\"https://www.coursera.org/learn/learning-how-to-learn/\">\"Learning How to Learn\"</a> videos. This is just about how to study in general. In the course, they <a href=\"https://www.coursera.org/learn/learning-how-to-learn/lecture/8IUbH/interview-with-dr-terrence-sejnowski\">advocate the learn-by-doing approach</a>, as we're doing here. You'll get various other tips that are easy to apply, but go a long way to make your time investment more effective.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-09-16T23:18:47.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"hangtwenty/dive-into-machine-learning","categoryHTML":"<h2>Deep Learning</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><strong><a href=\"https://github.com/humphd/have-fun-with-machine-learning\">\"Have Fun With [Deep] Learning\" by David Humphrey.</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/humphd/have-fun-with-machine-learning\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Ge